 p.&#160;51.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Talk+about+Sex%3A+The+Battles+over+Sex+Education+in+the+United+States&amp;rft.pages=51&amp;rft.pub=University+of+California+Press&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.aulast=Irvine&amp;rft.aufirst=Janice+M.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DjBWYvXt18CwC%26pg%3DPA51&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIs+the+School+House+the+Proper+Place+to+Teach+Raw+Sex%3F\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Mass, Lawrence (1990). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=tK4eM6ljgd4C&amp;pg=PA68\"><i>Dialogues of the Sexual Revolution: Homosexuality as behavior and identity</i></a>. Psychology Press. pp.&#160;68\u201369.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Dialogues+of+the+Sexual+Revolution%3A+Homosexuality+as+behavior+and+identity&amp;rft.pages=68-69&amp;rft.pub=Psychology+Press&amp;rft.date=1990&amp;rft.aulast=Mass&amp;rft.aufirst=Lawrence&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DtK4eM6ljgd4C%26pg%3DPA68&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIs+the+School+House+the+Proper+Place+to+Teach+Raw+Sex%3F\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Grummon, Donald L.; Barclay, Andrew M.; Hammond, Nancy K. (1971). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.google.com/search?hl=en&amp;tbo=1&amp;tbs=bks%3A1&amp;q=%22were+explicit+in+regarding%22+%22search+for+pers